SA Portal: passenger wallet admin (proxy + UI) + auth hardening

Original task: build SA Portal side of the passenger-wallet admin feature
(proxy + UI + nav + replit.md gotcha) once CUSTOMER_WEB_URL secret is set.

Shipped:
- src/routes/sa-wallet.ts — proxy for /api/sa-wallet/{lookup, balance,
  ledger, reconciliation, adjust} that forwards to ${CUSTOMER_WEB_URL}
  /api/admin/wallet/* with X-Admin-Key server-side (browser never sees
  the secret). Plus /_health probe (no auth, booleans only).
- src/app.ts — mounted saWalletRouter.
- taxitime.co.nz/superadmin360taxi/SA-Wallet.aspx — admin UI with three
  panels: lookup (balance + last-50 ledger), manual adjustment (controlled
  reason list, mandatory note), reconciliation (date range, byReason
  table, integrity check closing-opening === credits-debits, CSV export).
- replit.md — added wallet gotcha documenting ownership split, env vars,
  identifier resolver, audit recovery via auditTxId, integrity identity,
  adjust reason codes, Bearer-token auth, and /api/fb blocklist.

Drift from plan (after code review):
- Original plan used ?saUid= query-param auth (matching legacy SA-portal
  pattern). Architect flagged this as a critical auth bypass because
  /api/fb was unauthenticated and let anyone enumerate superAdmins/* to
  steal a UID, then pose as that admin against the wallet endpoints —
  a financial-impact bypass on a brand-new endpoint.
- Hardened to Firebase ID-token auth (Authorization: Bearer …):
  server verifies via verifyFirebaseToken(), checks isSuperAdmin() on
  the resolved uid, ignores caller-supplied saUid entirely, and stamps
  the verified uid into upstream calls as X-Admin-Uid header +
  adminUid body field for tamper-proof audit.
- Locked down /api/fb (GET + POST) with a small blocklist for paths
  starting with superAdmins, passengerWallet, walletAdminAudit
  (case-insensitive). Backward-safe: no SA frontend page reads these
  paths via /api/fb — confirmed by grep. Normal admin paths
  (e.g. superClients) still return 200.
- Fixed XSS in SA-Wallet.aspx ledger note rendering — `note` is now
  escaped via esc() before insertHTML, plus auditTxId fragment.
  esc() also extended to handle apostrophes.

Sidebar nav: each SA-*.aspx page has its own inline nav rather than a
shared include, so no global nav file to update. The wallet page links
back via SA-Dashboard / SA-Clients / SA-Drivers in its own top nav.
User can add a "Passenger Wallet" link inside any SA-*.aspx side menu
they want; pointed it out in chat as a separate small follow-up.

Smoke tests passing: /_health reports both envs present; no-token,
bad-token, and legacy saUid-only requests all return 401; /api/fb
blocks all 3 sensitive paths (403) but normal admin paths unchanged (200).
Architect re-review: Pass on all three previously flagged issues.
